Got it üëç
Here‚Äôs a **minimal Spring Boot service** that can send a simple Slack message (no PDF yet).

---

### 1. Add Dependency (Gradle or Maven)

```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>com.slack.api</groupId>
    <artifactId>slack-api-client</artifactId>
    <version>1.40.3</version>
</dependency>
```

---

### 2. Application Properties

```properties
slack.bot.token=xoxb-your-bot-token
slack.channel.id=C1234567890
```

---

### 3. Slack Service Class

```java
package com.example.slackdemo.service;

import com.slack.api.Slack;
import com.slack.api.methods.SlackApiException;
import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Value;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Service;

import java.io.IOException;

@Service
public class SlackService {

    @Value("${slack.bot.token}")
    private String botToken;

    @Value("${slack.channel.id}")
    private String channelId;

    public void sendMessage(String message) throws IOException, SlackApiException {
        var slack = Slack.getInstance();
        var response = slack.methods(botToken).chatPostMessage(req -> req
                .channel(channelId)
                .text(message)
        );

        if (!response.isOk()) {
            throw new RuntimeException("Error sending message: " + response.getError());
        }
    }
}
```

---

### 4. Example Controller

```java
package com.example.slackdemo.controller;

import com.example.slackdemo.service.SlackService;
import com.slack.api.methods.SlackApiException;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestController;

import java.io.IOException;

@RestController
public class SlackController {

    private final SlackService slackService;

    public SlackController(SlackService slackService) {
        this.slackService = slackService;
    }

    @GetMapping("/sendSlack")
    public String sendSlackMessage() throws IOException, SlackApiException {
        slackService.sendMessage("Hello team! üëã This is a test message from Spring Boot üöÄ");
        return "Message sent to Slack!";
    }
}
```

---

‚úÖ Now if you run your Spring Boot app and hit:
`http://localhost:8080/sendSlack`

A message will be posted to your Slack channel üéâ.

